==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sulphur-bottom
<hw>Sul`phur-bot"tom</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A very large whalebone whale of the genus <gen>Sibbaldius</gen>,
having a yellowish belly; especially, <spn>Sibbaldius sulfureus</spn> of
the North Pacific, and <spn>Sibbaldius borealis</spn> of the North
Atlantic; -- called also <altname>sulphur whale</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sulphureity</ent>⟦br⟧
